body:
As suggested by @gmaxwell : changed names from "SybilCheck" to "PartitionCheck"

He also suggested replacing the boost::math::poisson calculations with hard-coded constants to get rid of the dependency on boost/math/distributions. I think the purpose of the code is clearer doing the calculations here, and it is easier to update if "we" decide that 4 hours or 1-false-positive-in-50-years either need to change or need to become command-line params.

@sipa volunteered in IRC to write a little scheduler to avoid the VM overhead of another boost::thread, this will be rebased if that happens.

